    {
      "id": "1509176448223674489",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-05-27T12:48:24.399+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": true,
      "content": "\ud83d\udce2 It's been a while since the last update to the project template, but we worked on a lot of improvements in the background, which I'm happy to share with you now!\n\nAll of the wafer.space PDK changes have finally been upstreamed to [open_pdks](https://github.com/RTimothyEdwards/open_pdks), which allows us to sunset the wafer.space PDK fork.\nThis is important since we want one common target for community efforts and avoid unnecessary fragmentation. Many of the community-created IPs are already part of open_pdks (SCL, PAD, SRAM and eFuse libraries).\nYou can now use [Ciel](https://github.com/fossi-foundation/ciel), the PDK manager, to manage your PDKs. The project template will use Ciel as well.\n\nIn addition, I have enabled support for the community-created 3v3/5v I/Os, the 3v3 SRAMs and the 3v3 standard cell library in the template. Not all of the IPs have been tested yet, so support for them is experimental!\n\nGive it a try in this pull request: https://github.com/wafer-space/gf180mcu-project-template/pull/60\nI plan to merge it soon and would appreciate any feedback beforehand.",
      "author": {
        "id": "323371864074485771",
        "name": "mole99",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Leo Moser (mole99)",
        "color": null,
