      "id": "1509280353049776358",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-05-27T19:41:17.24+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": "2026-05-27T19:41:43.778+00:00",
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "I've hit a problem upgrading to this version of the template.  I've tracked it down to the new librelane version - if the only change I make is to switch nix to use the `leo/wafer-space` branch of librelane then I see the same issue.\n\nThe problem is undriven net errors, e.g.:\n```\nWarning: Wire tqvp_uart_tx.\\next_fsm_state$func$/home/mdb36/wafer-space/ws02-tinyQV/src/user_peripherals/uart/uart_tx.v:116$2738.tx_en is used but has no driver.\nWarning: Wire tqvp_uart_tx.\\next_fsm_state$func$/home/mdb36/wafer-space/ws02-tinyQV/src/user_peripherals/uart/uart_tx.v:116$2738.$result [3] is used but has no driver.\n```\nThis particular case is using a verilog function, and I tried changing the uart_tx module to remove the function (inlining it into the process that calls it), and that fixes that instance of the warnings.  So I suspect it's a regression in yosys.",
      "author": {
        "id": "691780627338625077",
        "name": "rebelmike",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "RebelMike",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "2026-05_media/49aaff687e56f04e7bbdedf0077bab75-7DDB4.png"
      },
